(note: MStruct requires in addition FFTW headers and libraries installed.)

TO COMPILE under Linux:

1) cd "this directory"
2) make -f gnu.mak wxcryst=0 opengl=0 fftw=0 shared-wxgtk=1 shared-glut=1 shared-newmat=0 shared-fftw=0 unicode=0 shared=1 debug=0 zdenek=1 mstruct_am

OR

1) open "clean_all_objcryst.sh" in the text editor and set "mstruct_dir" to your mstruct directory
2) run "clean_all_objcryst.sh" script and answer 2x Yes: ./clean_all_objcryst.sh

TO RUN with example nb. 1:

1) ./mstruct_am < tio2-film-stress1.imp > tio2-film-stress1.out

TO CLEAN compiled project:

1) make -f gnu.mak clean_all

//----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


